This article is a press gaggle by Press Secretary Robert Gibbs aboard Air Force One en route to Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. Gibbs addresses questions about the relationship between the US and the UK, stating that there is still a special relationship and that the media-generated rumors are silly. He also discusses the push for more balanced and sustainable growth at the G20 meeting and the importance of financial regulatory reform. Gibbs mentions the possibility of President Obama going to Copenhagen for the IOC bid and expresses hope that Iran and North Korea will follow the example of Libya in giving up their nuclear weapons programs.